content: I really like this game and play it all the time. My only gripe is that I've never been able to play an online game because apparently nobody is ever online and willing to play. I don't know if this is a glitch, or if the community of users is really that small. By far, however, this is the best Texas 42 app around. Very easy to pick up and play. Company occasionally makes a stupid non-human move, but that's not too often.
Multiplayer doesn't work on android

I'm an Aggie, so of course I learned to play 42 while in college. Absolutely love this app. Only issue I've run into is that even with forced bidding enabled, sometimes it allows all 4 players to pass, and it reshuffles. Update: downgraded from 5 to 3 stars because game play has gone downhill recently. Bot players sometimes behave as though they're trying to throw the game. To me, that means that the programming needs adjustment.
Not perfect, but pretty close. My partner makes a lot of dumb mistakes. Lol.
Aaaaa

My partner and I are ahead 6 marks to 5. My DUMB robot partner bids 2 marks(84). He goes set and the opponents win when a sane bidder would have only bid 1 mark. Who would ever bid 2 marks when only one is needed? PLEASE fix the robot logic. Thanks P.S. I love the app, but things like that are frustrating.
Good to brush up on the game
My partner play strangely, sometimes he play well. A lot of the time he plays strangely.

**UPDATE** 2 stars Please, please change the programming to make the A.I. play like they're supposed to 100% of the time. I can't tell you how many times I've lost a match because they randomly played stupid. **Original** 4 stars I guess I've played it so much that it has become predictable. It is very frustrating to play hands that in real life I would take a high percentage of the time, but here the A.I. will almost always have the perfect combination of dominoes that can hurt me.
What happened ?

Computer bidding isn't great. Force bid option doesn't work. At least once 
per game, everyone passes and the dominoes are reshuffled.

The multiplayer does not work. It should say that it does not work on the 
samsung galaxy 8.

Played 42 all my life and never got consistently bad hands like this app gave me. Maybe need new algorithms or something. Honestly, at least 30 to 40 percent of the time I looked at my dominoes considering whether I could go low. Most of the time if I did get a normal bid, I could expect to have at least three offs. I probably played 200 to 300 games on this app and only bid one or two marks (high) maybe twice. None of what I've mentioned happens like that in real life games. After a lot more frustration than enjoyment, I decided to uninstall the app. I'll try to find another.
Not perfect, but pretty darn good.
I guess nobody get on multiplayer? I've sat waiting for rooms to pop up nothing. I've created my own room wait for people and nothing.   Vs AI is fun but frustrating   Multiplayer needs to be fixed
Kept sending me back to bid in the middle of a hand. Deleted it
Good AI with good gameplay like the app. I just wish it allowed 7's.
Game is fun, works well as a time waster. Got it to play with friends but can't as they are on iPhone, please fix!
Android can't play online with IOS

Seems solid, good play most of the time vs the built-in players.  Have yet to try multiplayer.  One thing that would be nice is if multiplayer back-end was uniform between ios and android, so friends with different platforms could all play together.  Also, would be cool if app kept stats on your play, bidding success, wins etc.  But overall nicely-done, enjoyable app!

I agree with most,  easy to pick wrong thing.  But it Has some issues on  logic.  Several times it plays inconsistent.  It let my opponent go set when Opponent had the high domino and I only needed one point to set them.   Opponents don't seem to keep track of points,  that isn't the only time that happened.
I enjoy playing it when I am at Dr. Office

Definitely huge problem in placing wrong bid & trumps  in error, need a way to back out & correct it. Also would enjoy if Sevens bid could be done.  Would be 5* if bidding & trump back out could be added.
Good app. But too easy to hit wrong bid or trump. Must add way to back out wrong taps before I'll play very often.
This game SUCKS. Not 42. I love 42. Just get the free ap '42' not the $1.99 'Texas 42'. Better by far in every respect.
Thanks PJF!

I'm a huge fan of this App and played it for many, many months on the IPad version of the App. Unfortunately, this Android App is not as enjoyable because it quite often won't take my bid, the touch doesn't register. The press on the tile during play works fine, just the bidding doesn't work well.
Hard to tell what domino was played by who sometimes. Would like to play out hand sometimes.
Good graphics,  good AI.  Would get five stars, if there was an option to play out the hand once the bid was reached or set.
It won't accept my bid.  I tap my bid, my selection flashes, nothing happens.
I really like this game. The AI dies a good job of playing as it should. My only question is why can't I play sevens...

-The AI is pretty good  -The graphic design is fine, but feels older  -does not have a stats section like other apps  -Online multiplayer room is always empty, I ment find anyone to play -Developer was originally quick and responsive to bugs, but no longer is replying to posts on the Facebook page or updating the app.

Multiplayer mode is unusable because of bugs, such as freezes and bidding windows popping up in the middle of a hand.  In single player mode the AI sometimes makes really poor plays.  Example - Opponent 2 (to my right) won a 31 bid, aces are trumps.  Opponent 2 pulls trumps, then leads 5:2.  I play my only 5, the 5:0.  Opponent 1 plays 5:3, then my partner takes the trick with 5:6.  To my amazement my partner then led the 5:5, which Opponent 2 trumped.  Had my AI partner played the 5:5 on the previous trick (no gamble, his was the fourth domino) we would have set the opponents.  As it was they made the bid ... This is just one of numerous examples - it seems the AI sometimes fails to lay down points when any human 42 player would, even when it's a sure thing.  Still I'm not asking for my $2 back, the game has possibilities if the developer keeps working on it ... it's definitely better than the other Android 42 game out there ...

I love playing 42 but it's not always easy getting four players. This app is fun and easy to use, you can play by yourself with computer players, and with online multi play it makes it even more enjoyable!
Love this app. Great way to burn time when your free.  My wife loves it too.  I think that adding sevens would make it better.
Awesome game!

I bought this app solely for the purpose of online multi player capability. Yet, the whole week now that I've had it, I have not been able to play one game because there is never anyone else online! Very frustrating. There are free apps to play with bots if that's what I wanted to do, but it's not. Which is why I say this is a waste of money!
This is the only realistic 42 game app out there. I play it all the time. Well worth the $$
I tried for couple of hours last night and game kept freezing up or bidding icon would appear in mid game. Please fix or refund money. I want to play people..not computer.
It needs online play.  It would be great if you could easily play with Facebook friends.
Best 42 game out there.
Would like to see 7's added.
Fun app that works smoothly. Great introduction to the game of 42 if people havent played it before too. Look forward the android multiplayer.
Really fun, thank you

The AI is surprisingly good, except it is sometimes terrible when playing nello or just simple 30 bids.  Also, please remove legacy menu option and activate the back button. Would be nice if there was a way to push the back button and get a "Do you want to quit?" popup.
Waiting on Android multi-player, otherwise the app is awesome!
Best game ever made

I enjoyed the other app for what it was, but eventually the ai became too frustrating to play with. This one feels much more mature. Really enjoying it, and the brief time I've played has already justified spending a few bucks. I'm looking forward to new features and tweaks! Huge potential.
This is an excellent version of 42.  The AI is very good, the controls are straightforward and easy, and there are several different game play modes.  Great job, and thanks for making this
This is the game I have been waiting for since I got my mytouch3g 4 years ago. The best 42 game on the market.
This app needs a "quit" button and the ability to move app to memory card.
replyContent: I've granted permission to write to external storage.  Are you getting an error or something when you try?

content: Best game of bones out there!
